sql:
SELECT COUNT(property_id) AS total_properties_managed
FROM property_managers
WHERE manager_id = 0;

SELECT inquirer_name
FROM inquiries
WHERE inquiry_status = 'Open';

external_knowledge:
- Active lease refers to a lease that has not ended as of the current date (lease_end_date > CURRENT_DATE);
- Current property manager refers to a manager with no end date or an end date in the future (pm.end_date IS NULL OR pm.end_date > CURRENT_DATE);
- Leased properties are identified by joining properties with active leases.

sql:
SELECT inquirer_name 
FROM inquiries 
ORDER BY inquirer_name ASC;

external_knowledge:
- "Densely populated areas" refers to areas with a population density of more than 5000 people per unit area; 
- "Family properties" refers to properties that are preferred for families, based on the tenant_preferred column in the properties table; 
- "Cheapest properties" refers to the properties with the lowest monthly rent in each city.
